On Fri, 2 Nov 2001, George Lyle wrote:

> That should be enough for a freshly-installed nut.  If it is on there a
> while it can get rusted and be a real bear to remove.

I'm just full of suggestions tonight, or just not busy, but I've been
coating the threads of all the high torque and large nuts with Permatex
silver AntiSieze grease for over 20 years, and never have to wrestle with
these fasteners ever again. Especially the hub bolts - I coat the surface
where they sit in the rims also. 

